pplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert De St Omer was born about 0972, in France. She had at least 1 son with Robert De St Omer."},"et":{"about 0972–":"umbes 0972–Surnud","0970–Male":"0970–Surnud","1000–Male":"1000–Surnud","0972–Female":"0972–Surnud","0972":"0972","0970":"0970","Abt 1000":"umbes 1000","1000":"1000","about 0972":"umbes 0972","Flanders, France":"Flandre française, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 0972–":"noin 0972–Kuollut","0970–Male":"0970–Kuollut","1000–Male":"1000–Kuollut","0972–Female":"0972–Kuollut","0972":"0972","0970":"0970","Abt 1000":"noin 1000","1000":"1000","about 0972":"noin 0972","Flanders, France":"Flandre française, Ranska","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"about 0972–":"environ 0972–Décédée","0970–Male":"0970–Décédé","1000–Male":"1000–Décédé","0972–Female":"0972–Décédée","0972":"0972","0970":"0970","Abt 1000":"environ 1000","1000":"1000","about 0972":"environ 0972","Flanders, France":"Flandre française, France","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert De St Omer est née environ 0972, à France. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert De St Omer."},"de":{"about 0972–":"um 0972–Verstorben","0970–Male":"0970–Verstorben","1000–Male":"1000–Verstorben","0972–Female":"0972–Verstorben","0972":"0972","0970":"0970","Abt 1000":"um 1000","1000":"1000","about 0972":"um 0972","Flanders, France":"Flandre française, Frankreich","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert De St Omer wurde um 0972 in Frankreich geboren. Sie hatte 